Reasoning: The paper deals with logics and equivalence relations for Markov Decision Processes (MDPs), which are probabilistic systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also presents a model-checking algorithm for MDPs, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses partition-refinement algorithms, which are commonly used in the sub-category cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also deals with nested temporal operators, which are studied in the sub-category cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper discusses the branching structure of transition relations, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
